pr_body:
@solidsnack I just finished working on #3 and #4 and saw, that you have fixed #4.

My approach to backslash handling is a bit different, I check pairs of characters, where first one is backslash and second is escape character. Only `tnr\` characters can be used as escape characters. All other characters or no character at all (at the end of field) are threated as error.

Escape decoding is also integrated with error handling parameter, one can make errors pass silently (`error_bad_lines=False`), but by default it raises exception.

Py2.6 compatibility was sacrificed; also 3.2 is known not to work either (mainly because of v2 unicode literals).

I've tried to keep unrelated changes away, but couldn't resist on these:

- There's `boltons.compat.lrange` that always returns a list (makes a lot of code in `statsutils.py` cleaner vs `list(xrange(x))`);
- Saw `print "Deprecation Warning: foo"` and couldn't resist converting to use the `warnings` module;
- Made `six` an install dependency; IMHO it's a better solution than rewriting all of it inside `compat.py`.

I saw a lot of random test code inside `if __name__ == "__main__"`; mostly didn't touch that, this should probably be refactored into real unit tests.

The following is a working example

```
from spyre import server

class SimpleApp(server.App):
	title = "Simple App"
	inputs = [{
		"type": "text",
		"key": "words",
		"label": "write words here",
		"value": "hello world",
		"action_id": "simple_html_output"
	}]

	outputs = [{
		"type": "html",
		"id": "simple_html_output"
	}]

	def getHTML(self, params):
		words = params["words"]
		return "Here's what you wrote in the textbox: <b>%s</b>" % words

USERS={"alice":"secret"}

from cherrypy.lib import auth_digest #must import this to compute ha1 digest
digest_auth = {'/': {'tools.auth_digest.on': True,
               'tools.auth_digest.realm': 'wonderland',
               'tools.auth_digest.get_ha1': auth_digest.get_ha1_dict_plain(USERS),
               'tools.auth_digest.key': 'a565c27146791cfb',
}}

app = SimpleApp()
app.launch(config=digest_auth)
```

