This fix will let user generate `in_filter` expression while making calls in parallel from multiple threads.
```
handle.login()

def query_ls():
    mos = handle.query_classid("LsServer", filter_str='(dn, "org-root/ls-sp", type="eq")')
    for mo in mos:
        print(mo.get_class_id(), mo.dn)


def query_org():
    mos = handle.query_classid("OrgOrg", filter_str='(dn, "org-root", type="eq")')
    for mo in mos:
        print(mo.get_class_id(), mo.dn)

for i in range(1, 50):
    if i % 2 != 0:
        target = query_ls
    else:
        target = query_org

    thread = Thread(name=i, target=target)
    thread.start()

while True:
    if len(enumerate()) <= 1:
        break

handle.logout()
```

Timestamped geojson plugin cannot add style for features, so I've made them in properties.

Multi-colored lines can be :
```
features = [
    {
        "type": "Feature",
        "geometry": {
            "type": "LineString",
            "coordinates": l.coordinates,
        },
        "properties": {
            "times": l.dates,
            "style": {
                "color":  l.color, # Add geojson style
            }
        }
    }
for l in lines]
folium.plugins.TimestampedGeoJson({
    "type": "FeatureCollection",
    "features": features,
}, period="PT1M", add_last_point=True)
```
I've also added `add_last_point` option to turn off last point marker for each line's end.

